.SH "NAME"
MesaDrawingArea \- An Xt widget for Mesa/X with richer semantics
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The \fIMesaDrawingArea\fR widget is an extension of the \fIGLwDrawingArea\fR
widget which takes advantage of some features of the \fBMesa/X\fR
implementation of the \fBOpenGL\fR API.  
.PP
It also simplifies programming by associating a drawing context
transparently to the widget.  This feature is particulary convenient
in applications that have to deal with multiple instances of a
\fIMesaDrawingArea\fR widget.
.SH "Resources"
The following X resources are available in addition to the
\fIGLwDrawingArea\fR resources:
.PP
.Vb 13
\&  ___________________________________________________________________________
\&  |                    |                    |         |                      |
\&  | Name               | Class              | Type    | OpenGL attribute     |
\&  |____________________|____________________|_________|______________________|
\&  |                    |                    |         |                      |
\&  | GLwNximage         | GLwCXImage         | Boolean | N/A                  |
\&  |____________________|____________________|_________|______________________|
\&  |                    |                    |         |                      |
\&  | GLwNshareLists     | GLwCShareLists     | Boolean | N/A                  |
\&  |____________________|____________________|_________|______________________|
\&  |                    |                    |         |                      |
\&  | GLwNshareListsWith | GLwCShareListsWith | Widget  | N/A                  |
\&  |____________________|____________________|_________|______________________|
.Ve
.Ip "Boolean ximage" 4
Is \fIFalse\fR by default, setting it to \fITrue\fR will cause \fBMesa/X\fR to
use an Ximage (in contrast to a pixmap) as second buffer.
.Ip "Boolean shareLists" 4
Is \fIFalse\fR by default, setting it to \fITrue\fR will cause \fBMesa/X\fR to
share display lists among all widgets that have this ressource set to
\fITrue\fR.
.Ip "Boolean shareListsWith" 4
\fB[Caveat: This resource is not honored yet.]\fR
.Sp
Is \fI\s-1NULL\s0\fR by default, setting it to another \fIMesaDrawingArea\fR widget
will cause the two widgets to share display lists.
.SH "Utility functions"
The following utility functions are available
.Ip "void GLwMakeCurrent (Widget w)" 4
switches the \fBMesa/X\fR context to the one associated to the widget \fIw\fR.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
the \fIGLwDrawingArea\fR manpage, the \fIMesaWorkstation\fR manpage
